<task id="055" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.M6 — Communications tests batch 1 — COORD with x-email-communication-solution-r2</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, medium-tier, p23-m, bff-api, testing, communications, communications-coord</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-M</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Named Communications test files (1st half) are disjoint from sibling batch 056 (2nd half); also disjoint from already-compile-fixed Communications files (handled by Phase 1 task 011)</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair the MEDIUM-tier Communications tests — batch 1 of 2 (first half of
    `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/*.cs` files, EXCLUDING files already
    compile-fixed in Phase 1 task 011 which handled ArchivalFlow, AssociationMapping,
    AttachmentValidation, CommunicationService, DataverseRecordCreation per design.md §3.2).

    HIGHEST COORDINATION RISK: Per design.md §2.3 and project CLAUDE.md, Communications-related
    test files have the HIGHEST sibling-coordination risk because the `x-email-communication-solution-r2`
    project is actively modifying nearby production code. BEFORE non-trivial edits:
    1. Post sync to x-email-communication-solution-r2 owner
    2. Confirm no Communications production code changes are in-flight on their side this iteration
    3. Get explicit ack before proceeding

    For each failing test:
    1. Identify failure (orchestration assertion drift, response-shape change, validation rule change)
    2. Determine: `test-stale` vs `production-bug`
    3. Apply §6.2 trait
    4. Verify Pass

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY file's diff
    would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-055-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per §6.2, every touched test ends in `repaired`,
    `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, or archived. `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist with email/communications domain knowledge.</role>

  <goal>
    ~8 Communications test files (1st half, excluding Phase 1 task 011 compile-fixed set) end in
    §6.2 final end-state. Zero Failed. Coordination outcome with x-email-communication-solution-r2
    owner recorded.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="real-bug-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets a §6.2 final end-state trait</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-17">All MEDIUM-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
    <constraint source="§2.3 coordination">Daily sync with x-email-communication-solution-r2 owner; explicit ack before non-trivial edits</constraint>
    <constraint source="batch-partition">Batch 1 covers first half of Communications files (excluding already compile-fixed); respect partition</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §2.3 + project CLAUDE.md, Communications is the highest sibling-coordination
      risk area. Phase 1 task 011 already compile-fixed the 5-6 files in this folder that needed
      P1.A compile recovery. This batch covers runtime-failing Communications tests in the first
      half of the remaining file set.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="014" status="not-started">Compile health verified</dependency>
      <dependency task="011" status="not-started">Communications compile fixes complete (Phase 1)</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/&lt;first half, excluding Phase 1 task 011 set&gt;</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Post sync note to x-email-communication-solution-r2 owner — confirm no Communications production code changes are in-flight. Wait for explicit ack.</step>
    <step order="2">List `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/*.cs`. Exclude files already touched by Phase 1 task 011 (ArchivalFlow, AssociationMapping, AttachmentValidation, CommunicationService, DataverseRecordCreation). Sort remaining alphabetically; take first half → this is batch 1.</step>
    <step order="3">For each file: compute pre-edit line count; read failing tests + production code.</step>
    <step order="4">If any planned file edit would exceed 50% of file lines → HALT, file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-055-{FileName}.md`, await owner approval.</step>
    <step order="5">Classify each failure: `test-stale` vs `production-bug`.</step>
    <step order="6">Apply traits per §6.2; file ledger entries as needed.</step>
    <step order="7">After each file: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Communication"` (intersected with batch file list) verify outcome.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` with disposition + sibling-coordination outcome.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows NO production changes.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">~8 Communications test files (1st half, repaired)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md (entries if bugs found)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md (sibling-coordination outcome)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All batch-1 Communications tests Pass or Skip-with-reason; zero Failed</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff &lt;50% line replacement (NFR-02)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has a §6.2 final end-state trait</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No overlap with batch 2 (task 056) or Phase 1 task 011 file set</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">x-email-communication-solution-r2 owner explicit ack documented before non-trivial edits</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
